cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses techniques for reducing PAPR in multicarrier modulation systems, which are commonly used in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.COMM (Communications and Networking), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions system performance and complexity/cost, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
